Boil a half-full #kettle{}. Drain the @King Prawns{225%grams}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, fry the prawns, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw prawns. Cook so they're opaque in the middle.

Meanwhile, put the @Couscous{120%grams} in a #bowl{}.

Pour in the @Water for the Couscous{240%milliliter}, stir in half the @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%grams}.

Cover tightly with cling film. Set aside for ~{10%minutes}.

In another bowl, combine the @Cider Vinegar{15%milliliter}, @Sugar{1%tsp} and @Olive Oil{1%tbsp}.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add the @Harissa Paste{50%grams} (add less if you'd prefer things milder), remaining veg stock paste, @Tomato Puree{30%grams}, @Honey{15%grams} and @Water for the Sauce{100%milliliter} to the prawns.

> TIP: Put hardened honey into hot water for 1 min.

Simmer, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Next, add the @Baby Spinach{40%grams} in handfuls, making sure it's piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Fluff up the couscous and stir in the dressing. Share between your #bowls{}.

Top with the harissa prawns and spinach.

Crumble over the @Greek Style Salad Cheese{50%grams}.

Enjoy!